            <div class="welovestackoverflow" style="margin-top: 10px;">
                <div style="float: left;">
                        <p>
Modula-2 is a procedural programming language, created as a revision of Pascal. It was intended to fix shortcomings of Pascal which its designer, Niklaus Wirth, intended only as an instructional language. Modula-2 supports separate definition and implementation modules, coroutines, data abstraction, ...                         </p>
                                            <p style="margin-bottom: 0;">
                            <a title="tag wiki" href="/tags/modula-2/info">learn more&hellip;</a>
                            <span class="lsep">|</span> 
                            <a title="top answerers and askers in this tag" href="/tags/modula-2/topusers">top users</a> 
                            <span class="lsep">|</span> 
                            <a title="common, alternate spellings or phrasings for this tag" href="/tags/modula-2/synonyms">synonyms</a>
                                                    </p>
                </div>
